Move completely as possible as all the washing liquid before drying the beads. 6. Excessive drying of the Beads will reduce elution efficiency of the nucleic acid.

Inorganic Phosphorous reagent is an in vitro diagnostic medical device intended to be used by healthcare professionals for the quantitative photometric UV measurement of inorganic phosphorous in human serum, plasma and urine using the automated Beckman Coulter AU/DxC AU analyzers. Measurement of inorganic phosphorous is intended to be used as an aid in the diagnosis of bone and kidney disorders.[EN]

Inorganic Phosphorous reagent is an in vitro diagnostic medical device intended to be used by healthcare professionals for the quantitative photometric UV measurement of inorganic phosphorous in human serum, plasma and urine using the automated Beckman Coulter AU/DxC AU analyzers. Measurement of inorganic phosphorous is intended to be used as an aid in the diagnosis of bone and kidney disorders.[EN]

Cholinesterase reagent is an in vitro diagnostic medical device intended to be used by healthcare professionals for
the quantitative kinetic colour measurement of cholinesterase (CHE) in human serum and plasma using the automated Beckman Coulter AU/DxC AU analyzers. Measurement of cholinesterase is intended to be used as an indicator of insecticide poisoning, for detection of patients with atypical forms of the enzyme, or as a test of liver function.
[EN]

Additional Product description: Fagron TrichoTest™ is intended to assist health professionals in making patient-specific care decisions regarding the treatment or prevention of androgenetic alopecia, areata alopecia and telogen effluvium. It analyses 16 single-nucleotide polymorphisms associated with metabolic pathways predicting alopecia treatment responses and combines this data with relevant patient anamnesis to recommend the most appropriate treatment. Genetic data are obtained from commercially validated biomedical assays performed on DNA extracted from buccal swab. Fagron TrichoTest™ uses an automatized qualitative pharmacogenetic algorithm that predicts treatment responses and recommends the most appropriate alopecia treatment option in adult male and female populations affected by this condition. Outcomes include genetic results and personalized treatment formulas with suitable active ingredients and doses. [EN]
